Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *AI Engineer* position with your team. I bring over three years of professional experience designing and delivering AI-driven products — from LLM integration and prompt engineering to multi-agent orchestration and generative model fine-tuning — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade AI systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, applying prompt engineering and routing optimizations that maximized KV-cache hit rate — reducing end-to-end LLM latency by 60% and API costs by 50%. I also developed an MCP AI interaction layer integrating LLM features across 1,000+ platform endpoints, translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls for automated customer actions. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using LangFuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, and conducted code reviews and performance monitoring to maintain quality of AI-driven products. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I built an internal support chatbot integrating LLM features via LangChain and RAG with a PostgreSQL vector store — reducing ticket resolution time by 20% — and designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Python, taking it from prototyping to production rollout across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO. Together, these roles have prepared me to design, integrate, and scale AI-driven solutions from prototype to production, directly contributing to the core engineering responsibilities this role demands.

